http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/descript.value:
Hypoxia stimulates c-MET overexpression in HCC cells.
Although the hypoxia microenvironment may induce EMT, the hypoxia-related EMT cascade cannot be activated without the simultaneous activation of actin cytoskeleton remodeling via the Wnt/-catenin pathway.
Hypoxia-related EMT is also linked with the aberrant hedgehog pathway which plays an important role in maintaining the stem cell capacity of tumor cells.
Hypoxia could also promote the EMT of HCC cells via Twist1 upregulation.
